{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780128642111,"sessionID":"ses_1881128e0ffeiiErkDtN1kfFl9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_akLYKeziWJPWc9hdAvPp7310","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Iteration 2 — Q2 Focus: `dispatch-model.cjs` Generalization — Config Schema and Wiring\n2: \n3: ## Focus\n4: Q2: Design the `dispatch-model.cjs` generalization — how does config drive model/provider selection, what is the exact config schema for `modelBenchmarkConfig`, and what is the wiring path from `loop.cjs`'s `mode` to the resolved dispatcher?\n5: \n6: ## Actions Taken\n7: \n8: 1. **Read `dispatch-minimax.cjs`** (120/003) — the reference implementation, hardcoded to MiniMax API.\n9: 2. **Read 120/003 `loop.cjs`** — how it `require()`s the dispatch module and passes args.\n10: 3. **Read deep-agent-improvement `score-candidate.cjs`** — existing 5-dim scorer to understand the fixture-coupling risk (Q3).\n11: 4. **Read deep-agent-improvement `run-benchmark.cjs`** — fixture-based benchmark runner, anchor for understanding the mode gap.\n12: 5. **Cross-referenced iteration-001 findings** on the three-seam contracts, already partially answered Q2.\n13: 6. **Read 001 design spec** (`spec.md`, `decision-record.md`) — confirms `improvement_config.json` is the config locus; `dispatch-model.cjs` is a new file under `deep-agent-improvement/scripts/`.\n14: \n15: ## Findings\n16: \n17: ### Q2-A: Config Schema for `modelBenchmarkConfig`\n18: \n19: The exact structure for the `modelBenchmarkConfig` key in `improvement_config.json`:\n20: \n21: ```json\n22: {\n23:   \"mode\": \"agent-improvement\",\n24:   \"modelBenchmarkConfig\": {\n25:     \"enabled\": true,\n26:     \"target_model\": {\n27:       \"model\": \"minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\",\n28:       \"agent\": \"general\",\n29:       \"timeout_ms\": 600000,\n30:       \"max_concurrent\": 3,\n31:       \"rate_limit_backoff_ms\": [60000, 120000, 240000]\n32:     },\n33:     \"benchmark\": {\n34:       \"fixtureDir\": \".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/benchmark-profiles\",\n35:       \"profiles_dir\": \".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/assets/benchmark-profiles\",\n36:       \"minimumFixtureScore\": 70,\n37:       \"requiredAggregateScore\": 80,\n38:       \"repeatabilityTolerance\": 0,\n39:       \"thresholdDelta\": 0\n40:     },\n41:     \"rubric\": {\n42:       \"version\": \"5-dim-reproducibility-v1\",\n43:       \"weights\": {\n44:         \"structural\": 0.20,\n45:         \"ruleCoherence\": 0.25,\n46:         \"integration\": 0.25,\n47:         \"outputQuality\": 0.15,\n48:         \"systemFitness\": 0.15\n49:       }\n50:     },\n51:     \"budget\": {\n52:       \"max_iterations\": 12,\n53:       \"rate_limit_pause\": true,\n54:       \"rate_limit_pause_sentinel\": \"state/.eval-loop-pause\"\n55:     }\n56:   }\n57: }\n58: ```\n59: \n60: **Default behavior**: `mode` absent or `\"agent-improvement\"` → `modelBenchmarkConfig` is ignored. This is the backward-compat guarantee.\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ### Q2-B: `dispatch-model.cjs` Generalization\n65: \n66: `dispatch-minimax.cjs` is hardcoded to MiniMax. `dispatch-model.cjs` generalizes by adding an **executor dispatch layer** that routes to any `cli-X` binary:\n67: \n68: ```javascript\n69: // dispatch-model.cjs interface (generalized from dispatch-minimax.cjs)\n70: \n71: /**\n72:  * dispatch-model.cjs — model-agnostic CLI dispatcher\n73:  * @param {{\n74:  *   prompt_file: string,\n75:  *   executor: 'cli-opencode'|'cli-claude-code'|'cli-devin'|'cli-codex'|'cli-gemini',\n76:  *   model?: string,          // resolved from config if omitted\n77:  *   agent?: string,          // resolved from config if omitted\n78:  *   mock?: boolean,\n79:  *   mock_mode?: string,\n80:  *   cwd?: string,\n81:  *   timeout_ms?: number,\n82:  *   variant?: string,        // model-benchmark only; held constant for agent-improvement comparison\n83:  *   modelBenchmarkConfig?: object  // injected by loop.cjs for model-benchmark; undefined for agent-improvement\n84:  * }} opts\n85:  * @returns {Promise<{\n86:  *   ok: boolean,\n87:  *   exit_code: number,\n88:  *   stdout: string,\n89:  *   stderr: string,\n90:  *   attempts: number,\n91:  *   paused?: boolean,\n92:  *   pause_reason?: string,\n93:  *   mock?: boolean\n94:  * }>}\n95:  */\n96: ```\n97: \n98: **Executor routing** (the core generalization):\n99: \n100: ```javascript\n101: const EXECUTOR_DISPATCH = {\n102:   'cli-opencode': (opts) => opencodeRun(opts),\n103:   'cli-claude-code': (opts) => claudeCodeRun(opts),\n104:   'cli-devin': (opts) => devinRun(opts),\n105:   'cli-codex': (opts) => codexRun(opts),\n106:   'cli-gemini': (opts) => geminiRun(opts),\n107: };\n108: \n109: function dispatch(opts) {\n110:   if (pauseSentinelExists()) {\n111:     return { ok: false, paused: true, pause_reason: 'sentinel_exists', error: 'pause sentinel present' };\n112:   }\n113:   if (opts.mock) return dispatchMock(opts);\n114: \n115:   const executor = opts.executor || config.target_model?.executor || 'cli-opencode';\n116:   const fn = EXECUTOR_DISPATCH[executor];\n117:   if (!fn) throw new Error(`Unknown executor: ${executor}`);\n118:   return fn(opts);\n119: }\n120: ```\n121: \n122: `opencodeRun` maps to `opencode run --model X --agent Y --dir CWD \"prompt\"` (stdin=ignore). Other executors follow the same spawn pattern with their respective CLIs.\n123: \n124: **Mock modes** are shared across all executors — they are model-agnostic deterministic outputs used to exercise the scoring pipeline (same `high-score`, `low-score`, `default` stubs from 120/003).\n125: \n126: **Rate-limit handling**: backoff array from config, same 3-strike pause sentinel pattern.\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ### Q2-C: Wiring Path — `loop.cjs`'s `mode` to Resolved Dispatcher\n131: \n132: The wiring is a **config-gated injection** pattern that preserves byte-for-byte agent-improvement behavior:\n133: \n134: ```\n135: agent-improvement mode (default):\n136:   loop.cjs\n137:     ├── mode undefined/absent\n138:     ├── dispatcher seam ← candidate-source.plumbing().dispatch()  ← NO-OP (internal prompt, no CLI call)\n139:     └── scorer seam     ← score-candidate.cjs (existing 5-dim)\n140: \n141: model-benchmark mode:\n142:   loop.cjs\n143:     ├── mode = 'model-benchmark'\n144:     ├── reads improvement_config.json → modelBenchmarkConfig\n145:     ├── dispatcher seam ← dispatch-model.cjs (pluggable, loaded via require() or virtual module)\n146:     └── scorer seam     ← score-variant.cjs (ported 120/003 eval-rig scorer + 5-dim rubric)\n147: ```\n148: \n149: **Key implementation detail**: `loop.cjs` must not import `dispatch-model.cjs` at the top level when mode is `agent-improvement`. Use lazy/dynamic require:\n150: \n151: ```javascript\n152: // Inside loop.cjs — does NOT load dispatch-model unless mode === 'model-benchmark'\n153: const resolvedDispatcher = (mode === 'model-benchmark')\n154:   ? dynamicRequire('./dispatch-model.cjs')\n155:   : { dispatch: () => ({ ok: true, exit_code: 0, stdout: '', stderr: '', attempts: 1 }) }; // no-op for agent-improvement\n156: ```\n157: \n158: Or via a **dispatcher factory**, where the dispatcher module is selected at init time based on `improvement_config.json.mode`:\n159: \n160: ```javascript\n161: function resolveDispatcher(mode, config) {\n162:   if (mode === 'model-benchmark') {\n163:     return require('./dispatch-model.cjs');\n164:   }\n165:   // agent-improvement: return a no-op dispatcher that the loop handles differently\n166:   return { dispatch: noopDispatcher };\n167: }\n168: ```\n169: \n170: **Canonical config loading** (from both 120/003's `loop.cjs` and deep-agent-improvement's `run-benchmark.cjs`):\n171: \n172: ```javascript\n173: const config = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(\n174:   path.join(improvementConfigDir, 'improvement_config.json'), 'utf8'\n175: ));\n176: ```\n177: \n178: **The config path for deep-agent-improvement**: `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/` is the runtime root. The config lives at `../assets/improvement_config.json` relative to the scripts dir (or an absolute path via `DEEP_AGENT_IMPROVEMENT_CONFIG` env var).\n179: \n180: ---\n181: \n182: ### Q2-D: Backward-Compat Guarantee\n183: \n184: This is the key invariant that must hold after implementation:\n185: \n186: > **When `mode` is absent/unset/`agent-improvement`, the agent-improvement loop runs with zero changes to existing behavior.** The dispatcher seam receives a no-op (no CLI dispatch), the scorer seam uses the existing `score-candidate.cjs`, and `dispatch-model.cjs` is never loaded.\n187: \n188: This is enforced by:\n189: 1. The config default (`mode: \"agent-improvement\"` implied when absent)\n190: 2. The dynamic require / factory pattern that gates `dispatch-model.cjs` loading\n191: 3. A behavioral test: `loop.cjs --run-with-mode=agent-improvement` produces identical state JSONL lines as `loop.cjs` without the mode flag\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ## Questions Answered\n196: \n197: - **Q2 (answered)**: `dispatch-model.cjs` generalizes by routing through an executor map keyed on `opts.executor`. Config drives selection via `modelBenchmarkConfig.target_model.{model, agent, timeout_ms, max_concurrent, rate_limit_backoff_ms}`. The wiring path from `loop.cjs`'s `mode` uses a config-gated lazy require or factory — `mode === 'model-benchmark'` loads `dispatch-model.cjs`; otherwise a no-op dispatcher is used. Backward-compat guarantee holds because the no-op path means `loop.cjs` in agent-improvement mode never imports or invokes the model-benchmark dispatcher.\n198: \n199: ## Questions Remaining\n200: \n201: - **Q3**: Port eval-rig scorer + 5-dim rubric — harness + deterministic checks are fixture-coupled in 120/003; need to decouple so the same scorer works for both agent-improvement (profile-based) and model-benchmark (fixture-based) scoring.\n202: - **Q4**: Wire mode switch into `loop.cjs` (this iteration answered the config schema; Q4 focuses on the actual code changes to `loop.cjs`, `reduce-state.cjs`, `converge.cjs`, `materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs`).\n203: - **Q5**: Backward-compat test strategy + concrete implementation edge cases.\n204: \n205: ## Next Focus\n206: \n207: Q3: Port the 120/003 eval-rig scorer and 5-dim rubric — specifically decouple the deterministic checks + claude grader harness from fixture-only assumptions so the scorer seam works for agent-improvement's profile-based scoring AND model-benchmark's fixture-based scoring. Key risk: fixture coupling in `score-variant.cjs` where each fixture is a `.json` file with `requiredHeadings`/`requiredPatterns` against a SWE-bench output path.\n208: \n209: ## Graph Events\n210: \n211: - `{ type: 'node', id: 'modelBenchmarkConfig-schema', label: 'modelBenchmarkConfig JSON schema', relation: null }`\n212: - `{ type: 'node', id: 'dispatch-model.cjs', label: 'dispatch-model.cjs (new file)', relation: null }`\n213: - `{ type: 'node', id: 'improvement_config.json', label: 'improvement_config.json locus', relation: null }`\n214: - `{ type: 'edge', id: 'e-mode-001', relation: 'READS', source: 'loop.cjs', target: 'improvement_config.json' }`\n215: - `{ type: 'edge', id: 'e-mode-002', relation: 'LOADS', source: 'loop.cjs', target: 'dispatch-model.cjs' }`\n216: - `{ type: 'edge', id: 'e-mode-003', relation: 'CONNECTS', source: 'modelBenchmarkConfig', target: 'dispatch-model.cjs' }`\n217: - `{ type: 'edge', id: 'e-mode-004', relation: 'ENFORCES', source: 'noop-dispatcher', target: 'agent-improvement-backward-compat' }`\n\n(End of file - total 217 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Iteration 2 — Q2 Focus: `dispatch-model.cjs` Generalization — Config Schema and Wiring\n\n## Focus\nQ2: Design the `dispatch-model.cjs` generalization — how does config drive model/provider selection, what is the exact config schema for `modelBenchmarkConfig`, and what is the wiring path from `loop.cjs`'s `mode` to the resolved dispatcher?\n\n## Actions Taken\n\n1. **Read `dispatch-minimax.cjs`** (120/003) — the reference implementation, hardcoded to MiniMax API.\n2. **Read 120/003 `loop.cjs`** — how it `require()`s the dispatch module and passes args.\n3. **Read deep-agent-improvement `score-candidate.cjs`** — existing 5-dim scorer to understand the fixture-coupling risk (Q3).\n4. **Read deep-agent-improvement `run-benchmark.cjs`** — fixture-based benchmark runner, anchor for understanding the mode gap.\n5. **Cross-referenced iteration-001 findings** on the three-seam contracts, already partially answered Q2.\n6. **Read 001 design spec** (`spec.md`, `decision-record.md`) — confirms `improvement_config.json` is the config locus; `dispatch-model.cjs` is a new file under `deep-agent-improvement/scripts/`.\n\n## Findings\n\n### Q2-A: Config Schema for `modelBenchmarkConfig`\n\nThe exact structure for the `modelBenchmarkConfig` key in `improvement_config.json`:\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/iterations/iteration-002.md","time":{"start":1780128642103,"end":1780128642111}},"id":"prt_e77ef7011001rZ7XXRG10doVV4","sessionID":"ses_1881128e0ffeiiErkDtN1kfFl9","messageID":"msg_e77ef59660013hUsAePcOC4L5a"}}
